Former PIC CEO Dan Matjila will finally take the hot seat at the PIC Inquiry on Monday morning. • Editor’s note: Livestream above courtesy DStv 403. You can also watch it on DStv Now. JOHANNESBURG - Former PIC CEO Dan Matjila will finally take the hot seat at the PIC Inquiry on Monday morning. Matjila has been heavily implicated since the beginning of the inquiry. WATCH: More concludes testimony at PIC inquiry He has been accused of misuse of funds and careless investment decisions at the PIC. He has denied the allegations. Matjila resigned in November 2018. The PIC is the biggest investor in South Africa's economy, holding a large volume of bonds issued by the government and state-owned firms and equity stakes in some blue-chip companies. His testimony is expected to continue until Thursday.